    <note>Ma(2) Zun [1353] According to Yu Jing's, WJ, 20.12b funerary inscription of Zun's father, unnamed Ma(2) C [15487], the Raozhou, Leping xian Ma(2) traced their ancestry to Ma(2) Yuan [3671] of Han, a Fufeng jun Ma(2). At the end of the Tang, they transferred their registers (ji) from Huangmei county across the Yangzi to Raozhou and Zun's great great grandfather, Zhao [4212], and great grandfather, Liang(2) [4213], served in the administration of the Southern Tang. His grandfather, Xu [4214], and father, C [15487], did not hold office. I am assuming that all the Leping Ma are members of the same lineage and that Shun [15489] and Kangmin [15488] are at least lineage (third) nephews, Cun [15490] a lineage (second) grandnephew and Tingluan [15501] a lineal descendant. Tingluan composed postscripts for Zun's collected papers and calligraphs, and the colophon for Cun's jiaji. Jiangxi TZ, 21.12b; XCB, 176.22a; SS, 302.14a; Wang Anshi, WJ, 95.984-5. CBD, 3, 1829-40.</note>
